The paper discusses the use of search engines to locate missing web pages, which falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. The paper also analyzes the performance of web page titles, which is related to natural language processing (cs.CL) and digital libraries (cs.DL). The study of title changes over time could also be relevant to cybersecurity (cs.CR) and cyberinfrastructure (cs.CY).
